
He paused, the humorless smirk returning as he said, "She's afraid of me. Sometimes she's perfectly normal and we get along fine. But, sometimes she looks at me, and it's as if she remembers something...something triggers her memory, and the fear sets in. She's...She's afraid of me. And I've always known that there's a reason for it."
At first, the sour flavor in my mouth trumped all other senses. But as his words steeped into my brain, I found myself not completely unfamiliar with that feeling.
With Solara, with me, with Toivo, with Carmi. We'd all been adopted into this family, and after Solara left, our dads regarded us more differently than they ever had. Now, Rajy collected my hands into his and begged me not to abandon him like Solara.
"You never got to answer my question," Jason said. "How does the Ares reincarnation 'awaken' into power?"
Referring to himself in such a way suggested distance, that even though everything pointed to him being the reincarnation, he still didn't believe it. "It will fail unless you're changed of your own volition. No one can force you to become a vampire."
"And if they do anyway?"
"Then the prophecy dies, the world remains unbalanced, and the treaty is broken."




